This paper deals with privacy concerns in the sharing of energy data among microgrids, which is a topic closely related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes secure communication protocols, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of energy sharing, which can be considered as a problem in cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and game theory (cs.GT).
